import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='population', y='engineers', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the number of engineers and population in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="hurricanes", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=data['hurricanes'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Frequency of Hurricanes')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

data = pd.DataFrame({
    'state': ['Florida', 'Texas', 'Louisiana', 'North Carolina', 'South Carolina'],
    'id': [12, 48, 22, 37, 45],
    'population': [21.48, 29.31, 4.65, 10.49, 5.15],
    'engineers': [0.003, 0.002, 0.001, 0.001, 0.001],
    'hurricanes': [120, 64, 54, 55, 30]
})

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='engineers', hue='state', multiple='stack', kde=False)
    plt.axvline(data['engineers'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engineers across different states?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
